pr_review_comment_body:
instead of looping on each field and then using conditionals to understand which field to hide or show, you can simply call multiple css selectors, eg:

```javascript
var import_fields = $('.field-certificate, .field-private_key, .field-ecc');

if (operation_type === 'import') {
    import_fields.hide()
}
```

Could you please use
```
real norm = vec.norm();
if (norm > 0.0) {
  vec.mul(1.0 / norm);
}
```
instead? And remove the changes in `vector.cc` and `vector.h`. Thanks.

Is there any way we can punt on this concept entirely ? It seems a bit confusing with relatively little benefit.

For example, in Node (just like anything else), we just say "like all the other APIs, tell us which project you want", and keep the key concepts of Dataset, Job, and Table.

